<subSubSection box="[198,1279,1071,1098]" pageId="16" pageNumber="614" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1032,1523]" box="[198,1279,1071,1098]" pageId="16" pageNumber="614">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1071,1097]" pageId="16" pageNumber="614">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek &quot;glossa&quot; meaning &quot;tongue&quot; referring to the thickened upper lip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="614" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1032,1523]" pageId="16" pageNumber="614">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1110,1136]" pageId="16" pageNumber="614">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Eyes oval. Lateral cephalic lobe broad, with anteroventral notch, anteroventral corner subquadrate. Upper lip thickened. Mandible palp article 3 subequal to article 2; maxilla 1 inner plate slender, maxilla 2 inner plate without mediofacial row of setae. Gnathopod 2 asymmetrical. Pereopod bases distally narrowing. Epimera 1â€“2 without shallow excavation posterodistally, epimeron 3 serrate on posterior margin. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pearse" authorityYear="1952" box="[151,229,1265,1291]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Telsidae" genus="Telson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="16" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telson</taxonomicName>
lobes with shallow excavation distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1032,1523]" box="[198,1132,1303,1330]" pageId="16" pageNumber="614">
